.SH NAME
ata_sff_wait_after_reset \- wait for devices to become ready after reset
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ata_sff_wait_after_reset
.BI "(struct ata_link *link "  ","
.BI "unsigned int devmask "  ","
.BI "unsigned long deadline "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "link" 12
SFF link which is just reset
.IP "devmask" 12
mask of present devices
.IP "deadline" 12
deadline jiffies for the operation

Wait devices attached to SFF \fIlink\fP to become ready after
reset.  It contains preceding 150ms wait to avoid accessing TF
status register too early.

LOCKING:
Kernel thread context (may sleep).
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -ENODEV if some or all of devices in \fIdevmask\fP
don't seem to exist.  -errno on other errors.
